      <title>Product Launch Priorities</title>
      <link>http://thewestprogram.com/blog/647/product-launch-priorities/</link>
      <comments>http://thewestprogram.com/blog/647/product-launch-priorities/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Thu, 17 Nov 2011 10:14:41 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Bob Yeager</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Online Business]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Real Internet Business]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Bob Yeager]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Mike Silva]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[paul counts]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Product Launch]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[willie crawford]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[wso launch]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://thewestprogram.com/blog/?p=647</guid>
      <description>&amp;#160; Internet Marketing Product Launches Can Be Tedious &amp;#160; Hey there It&amp;#8217;s Bob. So, Mike Silva and I have been working tirelessly on creating a product launch, for the most part will create quite a stir on the Internet. Don&amp;#8217;t &amp;#8230; &lt;a class="more-link" href="http://thewestprogram.com/blog/647/product-launch-priorities/"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/the-west-program-blog/The_WEST_Program_Blog-Product_Launch_Priorities.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><center></p>
<h1>Internet Marketing Product Launches Can Be Tedious</h1>
<div class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 260px"><a href="http://thewestprogram.com/contentmultiplierwso/cmjv.html" target="_blank"><img class="zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured" title="Image representing Clickbank as depicted in Cr..." src="http://www.crunchbase.com/assets/images/resized/0004/9345/49345v1-max-250x250.png" alt="Image representing Clickbank as depicted in Cr..." width="250" height="158" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Image via CrunchBase</p></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p></center></p>
<p>Hey there</p>
<p>It&#8217;s Bob.</p>
<p>So, Mike Silva and I have been working tirelessly on creating a product<br />
launch, for the most part will create quite a stir on the Internet.</p>
<p>Don&#8217;t worry, I&#8217;m not selling you anything in this email, I just want to<br />
explain what we go through when we do something bigger than ourselves.</p>
<p>The launch is for a Warrior Special Offer (WSO) on the Warrior Forum. Over<br />
the past week, Mike has re-written the entire Content Multiplier in e book<br />
format, 100% revised</p>
<p>Step one complete <img src='http://thewestprogram.com/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif' alt=':)' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
<p>Step two was, figure out what we could give as AMAZING value for all who<br />
purchase.</p>
<p>That was simple, so we added Master Resell Rights for anyone who purchases<br />
so they can also sell it and keep 100% of the profits.</p>
<p>Our second component to the product was to go WAY overboard with value, so<br />
we are giving each person who purchases the Content Multiplier access to<br />
the recorded WEST Archives&#8230; and the rights to give it away when they<br />
resell the Content Multiplier, as well as they can transfer over MRR to the<br />
product as well.</p>
<p>Step two complete <img src='http://thewestprogram.com/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif' alt=':)' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
<p>Next up was to get a serious review of our product. Not asking for a bunch<br />
of testimonials or asking people to promote our stuff, but a serious<br />
critique of the product. So we asked the veterans in the Industry, Willie<br />
Crawford, Paul Counts and Micheal Savoie.</p>
<p>We didn&#8217;t expect the response (by the way, this is a long email that is<br />
laying out an entire launch strategy so you may want to print it up and<br />
save it, keep reading)</p>
<p>===================================<br />
Willie Crawford&#8217;s Response</p>
<p>===================================</p>
<p>Hi Bob,</p>
<p>I actually LOVED your product and look<br />
forward to promoting it. Please let me<br />
know when it&#8217;s up as a WSO since I don&#8217;t<br />
get over to The Warrior Forum as often as<br />
I use to.</p>
<p>Willie</p>
<p>If you need a testimonial, here&#8217;s one:</p>
<p>Bob, The Content Multiplier certainly lives<br />
up to it&#8217;s name.</p>
<p>Anyone can take this step-by-step blueprint,<br />
create high-quality content, distribute it in<br />
literally hundreds of places that MATTER, and<br />
pull in traffic from all over the internet.</p>
<p>You pointed out resources (most of them 100%<br />
free) that it would take the average content<br />
marketers YEARS to stumble across on their own.<br />
I&#8217;ve been creating articles, ebooks, books,<br />
videos, audios, press releases, etc. for 15 years<br />
now, and you showed me a ton of resources that I<br />
hadn&#8217;t noticed, and will definitely use.</p>
<p>Since you teach people how to actually create<br />
and distribute quality content, it&#8217;s going to<br />
attract pre-sold visitors, and the websites<br />
that you distribute the content on (as well as<br />
the search engines) are going to love this<br />
content for a long time.</p>
<p>Thank you for laying out a plan that will work<br />
long-term. A person can focus on implementing<br />
your blueprint KNOWING that it will work today,<br />
and more-importantly, that their efforts will<br />
continue paying off long into the future.</p>
<p>Willie Crawford</p>
<p>http://WillieCrawford.com/</p>
<p>=====================================<br />
Paul Counts Response<br />
=====================================</p>
<p>Hey Bob,</p>
<p>Thanks for sharing this. That is one awesome report! Here is a testimonial<br />
from me that you can use:</p>
<p>=====BEGIN TESTIMONIAL=====</p>
<p>&#8220;This report is full of meat and actionable content! If you take action on<br />
this simple strategy you can&#8217;t help but see traffic no matter what niche<br />
you are promoting. I have used similar methods before to get massive<br />
traffic, but I haven&#8217;t used everything mentioned here in this report so I<br />
know I was leaving good traffic on the table.</p>
<p>I will be recommending this to my subscribers and coaching students. It is<br />
an incredible ebook. I found that it was easy to read, follow, and<br />
implement. Even though many consider me an expert on traffic generation I<br />
still learned some things in here!</p>
<p>Here are just 2 easy ways to act on the content in side.</p>
<p>1) Just hand this report to your virtual assistant and have them go to town<br />
as it is very well explained. If you are someone that is running out of<br />
things to have your outsourcers do than hand them this report!</p>
<p>2) Sell this service to offline businesses for $750 to $1,000 each and<br />
